<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/49048608-steff-millington"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1498137703i/49048608._UX100_CR0,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/49048608-steff-millington">Steff Millington</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">This site is a way for people to keep track of the books they have read. When you click read it means you have read them in the past tense. If you wan<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">This site is a way for people to keep track of the books they have read. When you click read it means you have read them in the past tense. If you want to read it again you will have to download it or buy it or borrow it from the library. It's not a site where you can read the books online in the present tense, oh how the English language likes to confuse. Hope this helps :)<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
