  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/458799813" />
    <a title="C.G. Drews" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/11375137-c-g-drews"><img alt="C.G. Drews" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1521552918p2/11375137.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/458799813?book_show_action=true">Sep 23, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="C.G. Drews" class="user" itemprop="url" name="C.G. Drews" href="/user/show/11375137-c-g-drews">C.G. Drews</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/11375137-c-g-drews?shelf=young-adult">young-adult</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/11375137-c-g-drews?shelf=reread">reread</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/11375137-c-g-drews?shelf=paranormal">paranormal</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/11375137-c-g-drews?shelf=read-2020">read-2020</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/11375137-c-g-drews?shelf=audio-books">audio-books</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer458799813" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16377111333009158316"><b>[read 3 | Sept 2020]</b><br/><br/>I have no idea what happened to my old reviews but - wow. This book hits different at different times of your life. (CW for talking about suicide and depression.) I remember thinking this was the weakest in the series, too slow etc. But this time I just sunk into the prose, into the deep agony of the character arcs. This book is for broken people, for lost people, it is about <i>being lost</i> but also wanting to lose yourself. Damaged people telling each other to get it together be</span>
  <span id="freeText16377111333009158316" style="display:none"><b>[read 3 | Sept 2020]</b><br /><br />I have no idea what happened to my old reviews but - wow. This book hits different at different times of your life. (CW for talking about suicide and depression.) I remember thinking this was the weakest in the series, too slow etc. But this time I just sunk into the prose, into the deep agony of the character arcs. This book is for broken people, for lost people, it is about <i>being lost</i> but also wanting to lose yourself. Damaged people telling each other to get it together before someone gets hurt. Everyone felt raw and, often, made terrible decisions. But the chapters where Cole completely loses it -- he just doesn't want to be alive and in his head anymore -- made me lose it. Capturing the bone-wearying exhaustion and depression of not wanting to live anymore is hard to do in prose. There is no romanticising of suicide here. It is just depression: factual, ugly, grey. I really appreciated how it was handled, but it broke my heart.<br /><br />And just the softness? 🥺 I am old now, but I read Sam and Grace napping together, their hearts wholly entwined, and I am soft for them 😭 I love that his book is about this deep, unshakeable love and I will be an unashamed sap right now but it made me messy inside. <br /><br />I don't even care if "not a lot happens" on the page. It is a gorgeous book and just what I needed right now.</span>
  <a data-text-id="16377111333009158316" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


